  {
    "user": "UGWUJUZHT",
    "type": "message",
    "ts": "1735841253.289869",
    "client_msg_id": "f9194f33-18b9-4623-8da6-993c859e5b9c",
    "text": "FWIW: My knee-jerk reaction would be to work from the bottom up: feed your raw, manually-generated SVG to Claude and ask it to create a path on it from (x1,y1) to (x2,y2), then ask it to move a red dot along the path in NN seconds... I wouldn't ask it to generate the picture, only to modify the picture that you drew.",
    "team": "T5TCAFTA9",
    "thread_ts": "1735829846.211769",
    "parent_user_id": "U071NCA85JL",
    "blocks": [
      {
        "type": "rich_text",
        "block_id": "pbFpm",
        "elements": [
          {
            "type": "rich_text_section",
            "elements": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "FWIW: My knee-jerk reaction would be to work from the bottom up: feed your raw, manually-generated SVG to Claude and ask it to create a path on it from (x1,y1) to (x2,y2), then ask it to move a red dot along the path in NN seconds... I wouldn't ask it to generate the picture, only to modify the picture that you drew."
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      }
    ],
    "channel_name": "thinking-together",
    "channel_id": "C5T9GPWFL"
  },
